frameDefinitions: This frame describes assembly or construction actions, where an Agent joins Components together to form a Created_entity, which is profiled, and hence the object of the verb.
A Stimulus serves to bring about an emotion of mental stimulation in an Experiencer.
A particular Situation is likely (or unlikely) to result in a harmful event befalling an Asset.
This frame is concerned with the likelihood of a Hypothetical_event occurring.
In this frame either a Stimulus brings about a particular emotion or experience in the Experiencer or  saliently fails to bring about a particular experience.
The Temperature in a certain environment, determined by Time and Place, is specified.
frameExamples: Jack <t>built</t> a new house out of bricks.
You will not easily find a more <t>absorbing</t> box-set of piano discs.
It is <t>likely</t> that he'll arrive late.
It's too <t>hot</t> to do anything today.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> builds a <fen>Created_entity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Components</fen> that form the <fen>Created_entity</fen>.
<fen>Created_entity</fen> identifies the entity that is created in the act of building.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the building occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the building occurs.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the person, event, or state of affairs that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen>  can be described as having said emotion.
The <fen>Situation</fen> which may lead to a harmful event.
Something judged to be desirable or valuable which might be lost or damaged.
A concrete or abstract entity which may come to cause the loss of, or damage to the Asset.
The time period during which the <fen>Situation</fen> has the specified level of safety.
A particular location for which the <fen>Situation</fen> is safe. Frequently, it is to be inferred that the characteristics of the location make various <fen>Situation</fen>s safe or unsafe.
The state of affairs or occurrence whose likelihood is assessed.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the object or event which brings about the emotion in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where  it is a certain <fen>Temperature</fen> .
The temperature feature of the weather.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Temperature</fen> of the environment.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Temperature</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which an ambient environment has a particular <fen>Temperature</fen>.
The meteorological conditions which determine the ambient temperature of a locale.
listRoleExamples: Jack built  a new house <fex>out of old bricks</fex>.
Jack built a new house <fex>early in the morning</fex>.
Jack built a new house <fex>in a glade</fex>.
Most people agree, <fex>going over 100mph</fex> is unsafe.
<fex>Rain</fex> is fairly unlikely today, I think.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>today</fex>.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>in Seattle</fex>.
The temperature  was <fex>85 F</fex> in the shade today
It's like <fex>totally</fex> chilly, dude, like, totally.
We get warmer <fex>weather</fex> this time of year.

sourceCandidateSpans.text: The American Society for Testing and Materials
